eeded. I like the flavor brown sugar adds, but white sugar is perfectly fine too. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eI tend to use canola or vegetable oil but any liquid cooking oil will work. If your oil has a strong flavor, like some olive oils and coconut oil, this will impart that flavor to your waffles. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eYou can add 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon or \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/pumpkin-pie-spice/\"\u003epumpkin pie spice\u003c/a\u003e to add more flavor to this recipe. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eWaffle irons can vary quite a bit in size and how hot they get, so you will need to read the instructions of yours and experiment to get the prefect cook time.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/waffle-recipe/?tp_image_id=138794\" data-pin-title=\"Waffle Recipe\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-300x300.jpg 300w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-150x150.jpg 150w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-768x768.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-100x100.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-60x60.jpg 60w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-750x750.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-730x730.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-make-waffles-700x700.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content